        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 3:20PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 320 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles northwest of Bitter Lake Wildlife Refuge, or 17 miles north of
Roswell, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts up to 50 mph, and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of North Central Chaves County.

This includes Highway 285 between Mile Markers 116 and 137.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
